# Expo / React Native

## Packages

- Install Expo-compatible packages with `npx expo install <package>` — not bare `npm install` for native modules.
- Prefer Expo SDK modules (expo-router, expo-image, expo-file-system) over unmaintained alternatives.

## Project structure

- Use Expo Router file-based routing if the template includes `app/` directory.
- Keep screens in `app/`; shared UI in `components/`; types in `types/` or colocated.

## Styling

- Use React Native `StyleSheet` or the project's existing pattern — don't introduce new UI libraries without asking.
- Support safe areas (notch, home indicator) on iPhone.

## Data (v1)

- Prefer `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage` or `expo-sqlite` for local-only v1 data.
- Define clear TypeScript types for all saved entities.

## Don't

- Don't eject from Expo managed workflow without explicit user request.
- Don't add web-only APIs without platform checks.
